text: Oswald is an extinct town in Atchison County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. The GNIS classifies it as a populated place. A post office called Oswald was established in 1897, and remained in operation until 1901. The name Oswald may honor a local family. ==References== Category:Ghost towns in Missouri Category:Former populated places in Atchison County, Missouri
title: Oswald, Missouri
